yoruba_text: A dúpẹ́ lọ́wọ́ Jèhófà fún ìtumọ̀ tuntun tó ń mú ìyìn bá orúkọ rẹ̀.
english_text: We thank Jehovah for the recent translation that honors his name.

yoruba_text: Tí o bá rí oyin, èyí tí o nílò nìkan ni kí o jẹ, Torí tí o bá jẹ ẹ́ ní àjẹjù, o lè bì í.
english_text: If you find honey, eat only what you need, For if you take too much, you may vomit it up.

yoruba_text: Arákùnrin Stupnikov parí ọ̀rọ̀ rẹ̀ pé: Ju ti ìgbàkígbà rí lọ, ó ti wá dá mi lójú pé Jèhófà Bàbá mi lóye bí nǹkan ṣe ń rí lára mi torí pé ó mọ̀ mí dáadáa.
english_text: Brother Stupnikov concludes: More than ever before, I am convinced that my Father knows and understands my feelings.

yoruba_text: gbogbo wọn wá kún fún ẹ̀mí mímọ́, wọ́n sì bẹ̀rẹ̀ sí í sọ oríṣiríṣi èdè, bí ẹ̀mí ṣe mú kí wọ́n máa sọ̀rọ̀.
english_text: and they all became filled with holy spirit and started to speak in different languages, just as the spirit enabled them to speak.

yoruba_text: Àmọ́, ìwọ èèyàn, ṣé o rò pé wàá bọ́ nínú ìdájọ́ Ọlọ́run bí o ṣe ń ṣèdájọ́ àwọn tó ń ṣe irú àwọn nǹkan yìí, síbẹ̀ tí ìwọ fúnra rẹ ń ṣe wọ́n.
english_text: But do you suppose, O man, that while you judge those who practice such things and yet you do them, you will escape the judgment of God.

yoruba_text: Tí a bá sọ pé, A ní àjọṣe pẹ̀lú rẹ̀, síbẹ̀ tí à ń rìn nínú òkùnkùn, irọ́ ni à ń pa, a ò sì sọ òótọ́.
english_text: If we make the statement, We are having fellowship with him, and yet we go on walking in the darkness, we are lying and are not practicing the truth.

yoruba_text: Nígbà tí àwọn òjíṣẹ́ náà wọlé, ère tẹ́ráfímù ló wà lórí ibùsùn náà, àwọ̀n tó ní irun ewúrẹ́ ló sì wà níbi tó yẹ kí orí rẹ̀ wà.
english_text: When the messengers came in, there was the teraphim statue on the bed and a net of goat hair where his head would have been.

yoruba_text: Ní tòótọ́, wọ́n kàn án mọ́gi nítorí àìlera, àmọ́ ó wà láàyè nípasẹ̀ agbára Ọlọ́run.
english_text: For, indeed, he was executed on the stake because of weakness, but he is alive because of Gods power.

yoruba_text: Ọmọdé ò mẹ̀fọ́, ó ń pè é légbògi.
english_text: A child does not recognize a vegetable and calls it medicine.

yoruba_text: Ǹlẹ́ ọmọ mi.
english_text: Hello my dear.

yoruba_text: Torí èèyàn mímọ́ lẹ jẹ́ fún Jèhófà Ọlọ́run yín, Jèhófà Ọlọ́run yín sì ti yàn yín kí ẹ lè di èèyàn rẹ̀, ohun ìní rẹ̀ pàtàkì, nínú gbogbo èèyàn tó wà láyé.
english_text: For you are a holy people to Jehovah your God, and Jehovah your God has chosen you to become his people, his special property, out of all the peoples who are on the face of the earth.

yoruba_text: Hámánì wá sọ fún Ọba Ahasuérúsì pé: Àwọn èèyàn kan wà káàkiri tí wọ́n ń dá tiwọn ṣe láàárín àwọn èèyàn tó wà ní gbogbo ìpínlẹ̀ tó wà lábẹ́ àkóso rẹ, òfin wọn yàtọ̀ sí ti gbogbo àwọn èèyàn yòókù; wọn kì í sì í pa òfin ọba mọ́, wọ́n á pa ọba lára tí a bá fi wọ́n sílẹ̀ bẹ́ẹ̀.
english_text: Haʹman then said to King A·has·u·eʹrus: There is a certain people scattered and dispersed among the peoples in all the provinces of your realm, whose laws are different from those of all other peoples; and they do not obey the kings laws, and it is not in the kings interests to let them be.
